      { question: "Is the triskele the same as the triskelion?", answer: "The terms are often used interchangeably. Technically, 'triskele' usually refers to the Celtic triple spiral, while 'triskelion' can also refer to a three-legged figure (like the symbol of the Isle of Man or Sicily). Both share the underlying symbolism of three-fold motion." }
